The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Popat lone shuttler to make Athens cut Bhupathi, Hanley ousted Indian colts win Etoo best Diego dad ill Korea qualify
	 - MAY 1 DIGEST  Aparna Popat l New Delhi: Aparna Popat will be the lone Indian challenger in the badminton event of the Athens Olympics starting on August 14. Popat, world No. 23, is the only Indian to find a place in the final qualifying list released by the IBF. Indias hopes in the mens section centred around Abhinn Shyam Gupta and Nikhil Kanetkar but both failed to make the cut. l New Delhi: Top seeds Mahesh Bhupathi and Paul Hanley crashed out of the $990,000 ATP meet in Barcelona, losing in the quarter finals. Bhupathi and his Australian partner were beaten 3-6, 6-4, 6-2 by the unseeded Spanish duo of Feliciano Lopez and Fernando Verdasco. Bhupathi-Hanley had a bye in the first round and overcame the Argentine pair of Lucas Arnold and Augustin Calleri 3-6, 6-0, 6-3 in the second round. l New Delhi: India beat top seeds Australia 2-0 to win the Asia-Oceania zonal championship in the Junior Davis Cup in Colombo. Jeevan Nedunchezhian beat Matt Symons 6-2, 6-4 before Rupesh Roy overcame Steven Goh 2-6, 6-4, 6-4 to help India complete their campaign with an all-win record. The Indian boys had earlier sealed a berth in the 16-nation World Group finals to be played in Barcelona in September by reaching the last-four stage. l Yaounde: Cameroon striker Samuel Etoo was named African Footballer of the Year, becoming the sixth player from his country to get the honour. Etoo finished ahead of Didier Drogba and Jay-Jay Okocha. Etoo was rewarded for his performance in 2003 when he helped Cameroon reach the final of the Confederations Cup in France and scored a stunning goal as Cameroon beat Brazil 1-0. l Buenos Aires: Diego Maradonas father was hospitalised with a respiratory infection, a day after the soccer great ended a 12-day hospital stay for heart and lung problems. His father, also named Diego, checked into the institute Sacre Coeur, said a hospital spokesman. l Shanghai: South Korea qualified for the Olympic soccer competition with a 2-0 victory over China. Already out of the running for Athens, China were hoping to save pride.The South Koreans offered little chance, with Cho Jae-jin c driving home a perfectly timed header seconds before the break. Kim Dong-jin scored the second just two minutes into the second half.  Copyright 
